definitions.definition: To move into (an object), such that one ends up inside it.
To put on (an item of clothing).
definitions.example: I'm soaking wet. I need to get into some dry clothes.
The small child got into everything.

definitions.definition: To become involved or interested in (a discussion, issue, or activity).

definitions.example: How did we get into such a mess?

definitions.definition: To cause to behave uncharacteristically; to possess.
definitions.example: I don't know what's gotten into that child.
